========================================
Esearching.py
========================================
Usage: Esearching.py [options]
For example: Esearching.py -a gedit -t findAll -c PushButton -n Undo -C 0
Options:
  -h | --help        Print help information (this message)
  -a | --appname     Give application's accessibility name (Firefox, gedit...)
  -t | --findtype    'findAll' or 'find'
  -c | --ctrlname    Give the control's name you want to find (push button, menu...)
  -n | --elementname Give the element's name you want to find (Open, Edit...)
  -C | --children    Whether print out element's children

How to know appname:
If you don't know the application's accessibility name:
    1) just raise the application, 
    2) doing "Esearching.py -c application" to show all applications, 
    3) and check the appname from the <ElementName> list.

==========================================
UIEsearching.py
==========================================
Usage: UIEsearching.py

It's a pygtk UI application.

Preferences: to enable accessibility, and start at-spi-registryd process
Application Name: Give application's accessibility name (Firefox, gedit...)
Element Name: Give the element's name you want to find (Open, Edit...)
Control Name: Give the control's name you want to find (push button, menu...)
Find Type: 'findAll' or 'find'
Show Children: Whether print out element's children

How to know appname:
If you don't know the application's accessibility name:
    1) just raise the application, 
    2) click "Search" button to show all applications, 
    3) and check the appname from the list.
